An alternative representation of the PLQY(f,P) map is shown in Fig. 1b, in which the data points for each laser fluence P are presented as a single curve. Interestingly, the data points for each value of P follow a characteristic line with a specific shape. At low frequencies, and especially at high fluences, the curves are rather horizontal, yet once the frequency f exceeds a certain value, all data points start to follow a certain common dependency, at which the PLQY depends solely on the averaged power density W=fPhv\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
